    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Cut your<strong> potatoes </strong>(skins on) into chips, add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a small drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-chicken-breast-banh-mi-bao-buns/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, zest <strong>half</strong> your<strong> lime[s]</strong> and cut in half, then combine your<strong> red Thai curry paste</strong> in a small bowl with your <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>,<strong> ground coriander</strong>, a small squeeze of <strong>lime juice </strong>(save the rest for later!) and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>Vietnamese-style marinade</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>chicken </strong>to a baking tray (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!), drizzle with the <strong>Vietnamese-style marinade </strong>(reserve the bowl) and put the tray in the oven for 18-20 min or until charred and cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>Vietnamese-style chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-chicken-breast-banh-mi-bao-buns/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Crush your <strong>roasted peanuts</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> (if you don't have a rolling pin, just chop them roughly!), then chop your <strong>coriander</strong> roughly, including the stalks and strip your <strong>mint</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Slice<strong> half</strong> your <strong>cucumber</strong> into half moons and chop the <strong>remaining cucumber</strong> roughly</p><p>Peel your <strong>carrot[s]</strong>, then continue to peel lengths until you end up with a pile of carrot ribbons</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-chicken-breast-banh-mi-bao-buns/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>roughly chopped cucumber</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>carrot ribbons</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to a large bowl</p><p>Add the <strong>lime zest </strong>(not sure about citrus? Try using less!)<strong> </strong>and most of the <strong>chopped herbs</strong> (save the rest for garnish!)</p><p>Add a squeeze of <strong>lime juice</strong>, a small drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong> and toss \u2013 this is your <strong>carrot & cucumber salad</strong></p><p>Cut the<strong> remaining lime </strong>into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-chicken-breast-banh-mi-bao-buns/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wipe the reserved small bowl clean</p><p>Add your<strong> mayo</strong> to the reserved bowl with your <strong>sriracha</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>sriracha mayo</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-chicken-breast-banh-mi-bao-buns/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked, transfer it to a clean board and slice thinly</p><p>Pierce your <strong>bao bun packet[s]</strong> with a few holes and <strong>microwave</strong> for 1-2 min</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-chicken-breast-banh-mi-bao-buns/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To assemble, fill each <strong>warmed bao</strong> with some <strong>cucumber half moons</strong>, <strong>carrot ribbons </strong>and <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>Vietnamese-style chicken</strong></p><p>Top with some <strong>sriracha mayo</strong>, <strong>chopped peanuts</strong> and <strong>chopped herbs </strong>\u2013 these are your <strong>Vietnamese-style chicken b\u00e1nh m\u00ec bao buns</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-chicken-breast-banh-mi-bao-buns/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Vietnamese-style chicken breast b\u00e1nh m\u00ec bao buns </strong>with the <strong>chips</strong> and <strong>carrot & cucumber salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Serve any <strong>remaining sriracha mayo</strong> to the side and garnish with a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
